Section 1:
1 L.D. 819
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 TAXATION
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 526, L.D. 819, “An Act Concerning the
10 Status of Battery Storage Systems with Regard to the Business Equipment Tax Exemption”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'An Act to Clarify the Status of Energy Storage Systems with Regard to the Business
13 Equipment Tax Exemption and the Business Equipment Tax Reimbursement
14 Program'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §691, sub-§1, ¶F, as amended by PL 2019, c. 659, Pt. B, §2, is
18 further amended by enacting after the first blocked paragraph a new paragraph to read:
19 "Qualified property" also includes a battery storage system, as long as more than 50%
20 of the electrical output from the battery storage system serves load behind the utility
21 meter where the battery storage system is located or there was a fully executed
22 interconnection agreement between the battery storage system owner and a
23 transmission and distribution utility by January 1, 2025. As used in this paragraph,
24 "battery storage system" means commercially available technology that uses
25 mechanical, chemical or thermal processes for absorbing energy and storing it for a
26 period of time for use at a later time, including, but not limited to, lithium-ion batteries.
27 Sec. 2. 36 MRSA §6652, sub-§1-F is enacted to read:
28 1-F. Energy storage systems. Reimbursement pursuant to this chapter may be made
29 for battery storage systems, as long as more than 50% of the electrical output from the
30 battery storage system serves load behind the utility meter where the battery storage system
31 is located or there was a fully executed interconnection agreement between the battery
32 storage system owner and a transmission and distribution utility by January 1, 2025. As
33 used in this subsection, "battery storage system" has the same meaning as in section 691,
34 subsection 1, paragraph F.
Page 1 - 132LR1020(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 526, L.D. 819
1 Sec. 3. Application. This Act applies to property tax years beginning on or after
2 April 1, 2026.'
3 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
4 number to read consecutively.
5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment replaces the bill and changes the title. The amendment includes
77 battery storage systems as property that is eligible for the business equipment tax
88 exemption and the business equipment tax reimbursement program. In order to be eligible,
99 more than 50% of the electrical output from the battery storage system serves load behind
1100 the utility meter where the battery storage system is located or there was a fully executed
1111 interconnection agreement between the battery storage system owner and a transmission
1122 and distribution utility by January 1, 2025.
1133 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
1144 (See attached)
Page 2 - 132LR1020(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
